<!-- Description =========================================================== -->




    <br />
    <span class="field">Description</span><br />
    <span class="textrecord">
         
            
            
                LASERS (Light Amplification by Stimulated Emission of Radiation): Any <BR />

		
            
                 of several devices that emit highly amplified and coherent radiation <BR />

		
            
                 of one or more discrete frequencies. One of the most common lasers <BR />

		
            
                 makes use of atoms in a metastable energy state that, as they decay to <BR />

		
            
                 a lower energy level, stimulate others to decay, resulting in a <BR />

		
            
                 cascade of emitted radiation. <BR />

		
            
                 <BR />

		
            
                 [Source: The American HeritageÂ® Dictionary of the English Language, <BR />

		
            
                 Fourth Edition] <BR />

		
            
	    
        
